{"questionId":"2662367","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, solve <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>π</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>π</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid attempt to solve quadratic&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>recognition to solve for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>any correct solution from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">any correct solution from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>The previous two marks may be awarded for degree or radian values, irrespective of domain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;If no working shown, award no marks for a final value(s).</p>\n<p>Award&nbsp;<strong><em>A0</em>&nbsp;</strong>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;if additional values also given.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2662367","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.4b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, solve cos 2x=sin x, where -π≤x≤π.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Unit circle definitions of sin, cos, tan. Exact trig ratios, ambiguous case of sine rule","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.8—Solving trig equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}